soc: cix: require reset lookup consumer device names

reset_controller_add_lookup() requires both provider and dev_id fields.
Do not register CIX ACPI RSTL entries whose consumer device has not yet
resolved to a platform device, even when a con_id string is present.

---
diff --git a/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-resource-lookup.c b/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-resource-lookup.c
--- a/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-resource-lookup.c
+++ b/drivers/soc/cix/cix-acpi-resource-lookup.c
@@ -111,7 +111,11 @@ static int reset_lookup_handle(acpi_handle handle,
 			devm_kstrdup(dev, el[3].string.pointer, GFP_KERNEL)
 			: NULL;
 
-		if (!lookup->provider || (!lookup->dev_id && !lookup->con_id))
+		/*
+		 * reset_controller_add_lookup() matches consumers by dev_name().
+		 * con_id is optional, but provider and dev_id are both required.
+		 */
+		if (!lookup->provider || !lookup->dev_id)
 			continue;
 
 		reset_controller_add_lookup(lookup, 1);
